{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 01:43:20.544139", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\n- `host_1_1` and `host_1_2` are on the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet, but neither can ping the other.  \\n- `leaf_1` is on the 20.0.0.0/24 subnet (eth6\\u202f=\\u202f20.0.0.3/24) and cannot reach either host.  \\n- The hosts have no default gateway configured, and there is no routing entry on `leaf_1` that would forward traffic between 10.0.0.0/24 and 20.0.0.0/24.\\n\\n**Localization**\\n\\n- The problem originates at the network boundary between the two subnets.  \\n- `leaf_1` is the only device that could provide connectivity between the two networks, but its interface is on the wrong subnet and there is no routing configured.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n- Mis‑segmented network: the hosts and the leaf switch are on separate, non‑overlapping subnets with no router or gateway to bridge them.  \\n- Consequently, ICMP packets are dropped at the source host (Destination Host Unreachable) because the hosts have no route to the other host’s IP address.\\n\\n**Next steps (if mitigation is required)**\\n\\n1. Add a router or configure a gateway on the hosts that points to a device on the 20.0.0.0/24 network.  \\n2. Or re‑configure `leaf_1` (or the switch connecting the hosts) to have an interface on 10.0.0.0/24 and enable routing between the two subnets.  \\n3. Verify that the physical links between the hosts and the leaf switch are active (e.g., check link status on the switch ports)., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c9a8f953-2f2a-4da5-a406-f0b8daa69dea'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
